Hmm? US-Mobilanwendungsbenutzer folgen anderen #Weltmeisterschaftsteams ihres Heimatlandes mehr als ihrem Heimteam: http://t.co/5s5MfCHodu  Here's a breakdown of the translation:  * huh? (Hmm?) is a question mark used to express confusion or surprise. In this context, it's asking why or how this is the case. * U.S. (USA) is the abbreviation for the United States. * mobile app users (Mobilanwendungsbenutzer) refers to people who use mobile applications. * follow (folgen) means to follow or keep track of someone or something. * other (andere) is used to refer to something or someone other than the one mentioned before. * #WorldCup (#Weltmeisterschaft) is a hashtag used to identify posts about the World Cup. * national teams (Nationalmannschaften) refers to the teams representing different countries. * more than (mehr als) is a preposition used to indicate a greater quantity or amount. * $their home team (ihren Heimteam) refers to the team that is the home team for the users in question. * their (ihren) is a possessive pronoun used to indicate ownership. * home team (Heimteam) refers to the team that is playing at home. * : (:) is a symbol used to indicate a link. * http://t.co/5s5MfCHodu (http://t.co/5s5MfCHodu) is a URL that can be clicked to access the linked content.
